<HEADLINE>
IT'S OFFICIAL: BATES NO LONGER A PLAYER
</HEADLINE>
 NOTES-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN LYONS AND CLARENCE E. HILL JR. c.1998 Fort Worth
Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Forty-one days after an emotional news
conference to announce the end of his playing career, Bill Bates'
retirement finally became official Tuesday when Dallas Cowboys
management decided not to add the 15-year veteran to the club's
active roster.
</P>
<P>
   Bates had hoped he could serve as an assistant coach and play
with the club in emergency situations. But he learned Tuesday that
the team needed his roster spot to groom younger players. He will
continue to serve as an assistant coach, helping Joe Avezzano on
special teams and Mike Zimmer with the defensive backs. But in the
next few days, Bates will finally clean out a locker he has owned
since 1983. With that, he'll presumably get a full-time office and
a phone number in the coaches' wing of Valley Ranch.
</P>
<P>
   ``For the door to be opened to play was enough, but this
decision lingered on as long as my career,'' Bates said. ``There's
a finality to this and that's good. Another door has been opened.
This door \Rplaying\S is closed.''
</P>
<P>
   Coach Chan Gailey said deciding Bates' status was a ``hard
decision. The challenge for him now is to bring the same stuff he
showed on the field to his coaching. And I think he's done that.''
MORE ROSTER MOVES
</P>
<P>
   To get to the 60-man roster limit, the Cowboys released
linebacker K.D. Williams and fullback Dwayne Chandler. They also
reached an injury settlement with tight end Sean Simms (broken
jaw). BRIEFLY
</P>
<P>
   _ Cowboys coach Chan Gailey said that right tackle Erik Williams
will miss Thursday's preseason game against Jacksonville with a
sprained right foot. Williams will be replaced in the starting
lineup by Flozell Adams.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Cowboys began the indoctrination of cornerback Deion
Sanders to the new offense. Sanders, who has been out for the past
few weeks with a broken rib, returned to limited workouts Monday,
worked on some plays and pass routes, Gailey said, and he might see
some time at cornerback Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cowboys owner Jerry Jones said recently acquired defensive
tackle Artie Smith, whom the Cowboys acquired from New England for
a conditional draft pick, was expected to arrive at Valley Ranch
last night. Jones said Smith should see some action in Thursday's
game against the Jaguars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
