<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Where's the apostrophe?
 &HT;    Sidebar to CLIFFNOTES-MAIN
 &HT;    By Jeff Houck
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Does it bug you that that there is no apostrophe in Cliffs Notes
even though there should be? Well, for a long time there was, but
the possessive punctuation was later dropped. What's the story
behind the change? ``No particular reason,'' was Notes founder
Cliff Hillegass' brief explanation.
</P>
<P>
   The Top 10 Cliffs Notes
</P>
<P>
   There are 230 titles on the market now, but some are perennial
bestsellers:
</P>
<P>
   ``The Scarlet Letter'' _ Nathaniel Hawthorne
</P>
<P>
   ``A Tale of Two Cities, Great Expectations'' _ Charles Dickens
</P>
<P>
   ``The Great Gatsby'' _ F. Scott Fitzgerald
</P>
<P>
   ``Hamlet'' _ William Shakespeare
</P>
<P>
   ``The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn'' _ Mark Twain
</P>
<P>
   ``Macbeth,'' Julius Caesar'' _ Shakespeare
</P>
<P>
   ``The Odyssey'' _ Homer
</P>
<P>
   ``Moby Dick'' _ Herman Melville
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
