<P>
   JOHNSON-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Since I challenged the right-wing
hate mongers a few years ago concerning their character
assassinations of all who disagree with them, I have been deemed by
some a ``bleeding-heart liberal.'' How did I get this way? When I
removed all the ``teaching of men'' as instructed by Jesus's
teaching, and revisited his words, it was obvious. (Johnson, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MCLEESE-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ On school vacations, TAAS tests
and family reunions, readers respond: (comments from readers
follow). (McLeese, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ GLEN ROSE, Texas _ Like turtles on a log, the
men sat side by side on park benches. We parked our motorcycles
next to an old pickup that had the tailgate down to show off a nice
load of watermelons. We nodded at the men and crossed the street
for a cup of coffee. When we returned, we decided to sit a while
with the men. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WALKER-COLUMN _ Of the 12-year-old boys polled in my most recent
survey of the American people who live at my house regarding
President Clinton's television revelations Monday, 100 percent of
respondents said, ``He didn't say he was sorry.'' The five of us
watched together, and no one had much comment immediately
afterward. Maybe we were hoping it was all over. (Walker, Longview
News-Journal) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Crime. If you conducted a poll,
most people would come out against it. But let's be honest. People
love to watch crime being fought because, gosh darn it, it's fun,
cheap entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   Call it Toni Hinojosa's big day. (Kelso, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CSIBLEY-COLUMN _ Comes now Marianne Gilbert of Gainesville,
Georgia with some pages from a book she likes very much called
``Simple Abundance: A Day Book of Comfort and Joy.'' The pages she
sent me are about the pleasure of old books. She wrote that she
sent different pages to different friends, but knowing my pleasure
in old books, she sacrificed and tore the pages right out. (Sibley,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED 8/25.
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ I'm thankful for Bonnie, the hurricane that
doesn't affect me, me, me anymore, not just because she came and
went so unceremoniously. Bonnie, as it turns out, had a big effect
on my life.
</P>
<P>
   She gave me the thinking time to advance a new theory I have
about human behavior in South Florida. (Minor, Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
</P>
