<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   ``A Night to Remember'' _ (1958) 8 p.m. AMC (2593935) _ Tired of
watching Leonardo DiCaprio go down with the ship? Check out this
historical drama from Britain, which set a standard for special
effects in its re-creation of the 1912 ``Titanic'' tragedy. 125
minutes. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ``Vis-a-Vis: Beyond the Veil'' _ 9 p.m. WPBA (72596) _ Deborah
Wiley of Washington and Sima Daad of Tehran, Iran, have a
face-to-face conversation via satellite to begin bridging the gap
between the cultures of America and Iran. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   ``Wild Islands'' _ 8 p.m. WPBA (71813) _ Visit the Galapagos
Islands and other remote Pacific outposts of exotic flora and fauna
that inspired Charles Darwin's theory of evolution.
</P>
<P>
   ``Carrie'' _ (1976) 8:05 p.m. TBS (63241726) _ Based on the
Stephen King novel and directed by Brian De Palma before he went
off the deep end, this horror movie about a teenage misfit (Sissy
Spacek) with psychokinetic powers and a bugged-out mother (Piper
Laurie) is still a wonderful fright. Look out for a post-Groundhogs
John Travolta as one of the taunting teens who gets his
comeuppance. 125 minutes. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ``Soul Food''_ (1997) 9 p.m. HBO (436146) _ The cable debut of a
touchingly tasty drama about an African-American family that
weathers hard times with love, courage and a piping-hot platter of
fried chicken. Stars Vanessa L. Williams, Nia Long and Vivica A.
Fox. 120 minutes. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ``Lolita'' _ (1997) 9 p.m. Showtime (4399271) _ Repeat of the
long-delayed, much-disputed film directed by Adrian Lyne and based
on the Vladimir Nabakov novel. Jeremy Irons is at his jittery best
playing an English college professor who has an illicit affair with
a pre-pubescent nymphet. Impish newcomer Dominique Swain stars in
the title role. 135 minutes. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   ``The Exorcist'' _ (1973) Noon A&AMP;E (166634) _ Simply one of the
best horror movies ever made. Linda Blair stars as an innocent
12-year-old possessed by a demon with a bad attitude and a penchant
for pea soup. A quarter-century after its theatrical debut, it's
still head-spinning, bed-raising fun. Watch with a friend. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ``Diana's Funeral: BBC Coverage'' _ 1 p.m. WGTV (618653) _ A
rebroadcast of the entire three-hour funeral in London. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ``The Great Depression'' _ 2 p.m. on The History Channel
(8507905 , 4282011) _ Two-part documentary revisits America's worst
and longest economic collapse. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ``The Untouchables'' _ (1987) 4 p.m. WATL (119617) _ Stylish and
visually stunning crime drama about the famed crimefighters,
starring an Armani-clad Kevin Costner as G-man Elliot Ness. Also
stars Andy Garcia, Sean Connery and Robert De Niro as mob boss Al
Capone, who doesn't walk quietly but carries a very big stick. 120
minutes. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ``Love, Lust &AMP; Marriage'' _ 9 p.m. WSB (3127) _ ABC's
common-sense reporter John Stossel looks at cheating and adultery
at a time when that's all we seem to be talking about. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TELEVISION
</P>
<P>
   TV-DREAMON _ They're back! Brian Benben of cable's wacko ``Dream
On,'' has his own show -- aptly titled ``The Benben Show'' on CBS.
(Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
