<HEADLINE>
LIVING IN A FANTASY WORLD
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Online versions of NFL fantasy leagues have become so esoteric
that it's never too early to sort things out.
</P>
<P>
   (That's a hint: Get yourself in gear if you want to play one of
these things before the Sept. 6 opening kickoff.)
</P>
<P>
   There are several methods of compiling fantasy teams, then
competing with other cybersaps and monitoring the whole thing on
the Web. Some sites offer as many as three ways to play the league.
</P>
<P>
   Just be careful out there. Not all states allow playing these
games for prizes (in California it's OK). And because new
government regulations aimed at eliminating gambling on the
Internet might soon go into effect, all leagues must charge a fee
if they are to give out prizes.
</P>
<P>
   A sample of the range that's available:
</P>
<P>
   __ Yahoo!:
</P>
<P>
   Address: http://fantasy.yahoo.com/nfl/start
</P>
<P>
   Cost: Free.
</P>
<P>
   Prizes: None (that's why it's free)
</P>
<P>
   Deadline: Sept. 3, 8 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   Summary: Touts its game as one with ``no petty entry fees,
annoying transaction charges or hidden registration costs.'' Which
translates to no prizes.
</P>
<P>
   __ CNN/SI:
</P>
<P>
   Address: http://www.cnnsi.com/fantasyfootball/
</P>
<P>
   Cost: $19.95 (includes eight ``free'' issues of Sports
Illustrated).
</P>
<P>
   Prizes: $3,000 ski trip to Salt Lake City, personal computers,
autographed collectibles.
</P>
<P>
   Deadline: Sept. 2, 9 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   Summary: Can also play by mail.
</P>
<P>
   __ CBS SportsLine:
</P>
<P>
   Address: http://fantasyfootball.commissioner.com/
</P>
<P>
   Cost: $19.95 (also $99.95 for private leagues)
</P>
<P>
   Prizes: $3,000 home-entertainment center (grand prize), Joe
Namath autographed footballs.
</P>
<P>
   Deadline: Sept. 5, 11:59 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Summary: Players seem to appreciate what they get on this site
as far as information to help make roster moves.
</P>
<P>
   __ ESPN SportsZone:
</P>
<P>
   Address: http://games-espn.sportszone.com/
</P>
<P>
   Cost: $29.95 for first-timers, discounts apply in some cases. No
transaction fees.
</P>
<P>
   Prizes: $3,000 home-entertainment center (grand prize), ESPN
jackets.
</P>
<P>
   Deadline: Sept. 3, noon.
</P>
<P>
   Summary: Also offers late-season franchises (by Oct. 2).
</P>
<P>
   __ The Sporting News:
</P>
<P>
   Address: http://games.sportingnews.com/nfl/
</P>
<P>
   Cost: $59.95, with fees for roster moves ($2.50), adding new
players ($7.50) and adding new taxi squad players ($5).
</P>
<P>
   Prizes: $25,000 grand prize, $5,000 trip to the Super Bowl,
$4,000 trip to the Pro Bowl, $1,000 big-screen TV.
</P>
<P>
   Deadline: Sept. 4, 9 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Summary: Are you serious? No novices allowed. The stakes are
higher and the draft picks are assigned salaries that go against a
salary cap. Can also be played by mail or America Online.
</P>
