investigation of the president. By Don Van Natta.
</P>
<P>
   ARTS-IVEY (Washington) _ Bill Ivey, head of the National
Endowment for the Arts, thinks of it as a New Deal without the
Depression: an emerging era of murals and music for an arts agency
that until recently seemed slated for extinction. Just two months
after arriving from Nashville, where he ran the Country Music
Foundation for 27 years, Ivey is looking at more money and less
rancor from a Congress whose staunchest conservatives now seem at
least open to this Middle American folk musician. By Melinda
Henneberger. (1300 words)
</P>
<P>
   KING-RENO (Washington) _ Attorney General Reno announces a
