</P>
<P>
   HURRICANE-BONNIE (Wilmington, N.C.) _ Tropical storm-force wind
and rain lashed the Atlantic coast Wednesday as the edge of massive
Hurricane Bonnie reached the mainland. More than a half-million
people had been ordered to flee. The heart of the 400-mile-wide
storm, with sustained winds of 115 mph, could reach the mouth of
the Cape Fear River south of Wilmington between noon and 2 p.m.
today. By Kevin Sack.
