   EDs: MOVED Tuesday, Aug. 25, in both the (i) International and
(k) Commentary categories for use Thursday, Aug. 27.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   KING-DREAM _ WASHINGTON _ In the 35 years since Dr. Martin
Luther King Jr. delivered his ``I Have a Dream'' speech at the
Lincoln Memorial, how have economic and social conditions changed
for African Americans? A look at the story told by Census Bureau
data. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
