turn together.
 &HT;    But unless a definitive course is set to achieve these changes,
an open economy will never be effective, and stabilization will
never be achieved. Merely giving cash now while Russia burns is a
waste.
 &HT;     (c.1998 MSNBC News and the Center for War, Peace and the News
<TEXT>
Media of New York University) &LR;
<P>
   &UR; (Economist Grigory Yavlinsky is leader of the Yabloko Party, a
democratic reform party in Russia) &LR;
</P>
