<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-WEEKEND27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    This Weekend on TV
 &HT;    By Lyle V. Harris
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``A Night to Remember'' (1958) 8 p.m. EDT, AMC _ Tired of
watching Leonardo DiCaprio go down with the ship? Check out this
historical drama from Britain, which set a standard for special
effects in its re-creation of the 1912 ``Titanic'' tragedy. 125
minutes.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Vis-a-Vis: Beyond the Veil'' (PBS, check local listings)_
Deborah Wiley of Washington and Sima Daad of Tehran, Iran, have a
face-to-face conversation via satellite to begin bridging the gap
between the cultures of America and Iran.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Wild Islands'' (PBS, check local listings)) _ Visit the
Galapagos Islands and other remote Pacific outposts of exotic flora
and fauna that inspired Charles Darwin's theory of evolution.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Carrie''(1976) 8:05 p.m. EDT, TBS _ Based on the Stephen
King novel and directed by Brian De Palma before he went off the
deep end, this horror movie about a teenage misfit (Sissy Spacek)
with psychokinetic powers and a bugged-out mother (Piper Laurie) is
still a wonderful fright. Look out for a post-Groundhogs John
Travolta as one of the taunting teens who gets his comeuppance. 125
minutes.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Soul Food'' (1997) 9 p.m. EDT, HBO _ The cable debut of a
touchingly tasty drama about an African-American family that
weathers hard times with love, courage and a piping-hot platter of
fried chicken. Stars Vanessa L. Williams, Nia Long and Vivica A.
Fox. 120 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Lolita'' (1997) 9 p.m. EDT, Showtime _ Repeat of the
long-delayed, much-disputed film directed by Adrian Lyne and based
on the Vladimir Nabakov novel. Jeremy Irons is at his jittery best
playing an English college professor who has an illicit affair with
a pre-pubescent nymphet. Impish newcomer Dominique Swain stars in
the title role. 135 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Exorcist'' (1973) Noon EDT, A&AMP;E _ Simply one of the
best horror movies ever made. Linda Blair stars as an innocent
12-year-old possessed by a demon with a bad attitude and a penchant
for pea soup. A quarter-century after its theatrical debut, it's
still head-spinning, bed-raising fun. Watch with a friend. 150
minutes.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Diana's Funeral: BBC Coverage'' (PBS, check local
listings)_ A rebroadcast of the entire three-hour funeral in
London.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Great Depression'' 2 p.m. EDT on The History Channel _
Two-part documentary revisits America's worst and longest economic
collapse.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Love, Lust &AMP; Marriage'' 9 p.m. EDT, ABC_ ABC's common-sense
reporter John Stossel looks at cheating and adultery at a time when
that's all we seem to be talking about.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
