<P>
   FBN-COWBOYS _ Like a chain smoker who can't live without the
next cigarette, the Dallas Cowboys can't get rid of a nasty habit.
Losing. Dating back to last season, the Cowboys have lost nine
straight games. By any measuring stick, the team that won three
Super Bowls in a four-year span has forgotten what it's like to
win. Today's preseason game against one of the top teams in the
AFC, Jacksonville, might be meaningless in the standings, but it's
important the Cowboys gain some confidence before the real season
starts in 10 days. (Cantu, Austin America n-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m.
ET.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-IRL-STEWART _ At the peak of a great racing career, about to
make the jump from open wheel racing to the world's hottest racing
circuit, NASCAR, Tony Stewart should be coming into Atlanta for
this week's Atlanta 500 Classic looking forward to givng AMS a
whirl, even though his ride is an Indy car. Stewart, in fact, is an
angry young man with something to prove. Running third Friday night
at Bristol with 11 laps to go, Stewart was knocked out of the race
with the massive crash caused by Buckshot Jones. Then, on Monday,
he learned he was penalized 15 points on the Indy points
championship. (Mitchell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m.
ET.
</P>
