all the things you've taken for granted. Like when a batter is out
at first. He hits the ball, a fielder throws him out. James the
Third wanted an explanation. (Bisher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BENGALS-BLAKE _ CINCINNATI _ Deposed quarterback Jeff Blake
slipped into his sneakers, fastened the belt on his blue jean
shorts, tugged on the bill of his white New York Yankees cap and
headed for the door at Spinney Field. Team president and general
manager Mike Brown refused to confirm if he has asked Blake to
renegotiate a contract that calls for $1.9 million in '98 and $2.65
million in '99. ``I'm not going to get into that right now,'' Brown
said. (Ludwig, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
