AMWEST-FINE (Phoenix) - An internal FAA memo shows that the agency
documented serious problems in America West Airlines maintenance
operations beginning in 1995, and that the agency gave the airline
two ``fresh starts'' before finally hitting America West with a
record fine this summer. The memo contradicts statements by America
West that the FAA's fine resulted mainly from problems of
paperwork, and raises new questions about the airline's decision to
contract its maintenance to an outside company. The memo is part of
the hundreds of pages of FAA documents The Arizona Republic
obtained through the Freedom of Information Act. By
