<P>
   CLINTON-INVESTIGATION (Washington) _ Plans by the House
leadership to keep independent counsel Kenneth Starr's report under
wraps drew a sharp rebuke from House Majority Whip Tom DeLay, a
Texas Republican who said the report of President Clinton's affair
and alleged cover-up should be made public once the report arrives
at the Capitol. By JOHN C. HENRY. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   KING-PROBE (Washington) _ Attorney General Janet Reno says the
Justice Department will begin a limited investigation into the 1968
assassination of the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. amid claims that
confessed killer James Early Ray did not action alone. By STEVE
LASH. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   FIGHTING-TERRORISM (Washington) _ The United States must
increase its reward for the capture of Osama bin Laden, accused of
masterminding the bombing of U.S. embassies in East Africa, says an
Israeli expert on terrorism, Ehud Sprinzak. By NICOLE TSONG.
(Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SCANDAL-DEMS (Minneapolis) _ Rep. Richard A. Gephardt, D-Mo., is
making the rounds of key contested districts for the fall election
campaign. The House Democratic leader has continued to criticize
President Clinton for his behavior in the Monica Lewinsky affair.
By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   FLOOD-DISASTER (Del Rio, Texas) _ Gov. George W. Bush tours the
South Texas town of Del Rio, which was devastated by flooding along
the Rio Grande. Meanwhile, President Clinton declares a disaster in
the region, making federal assistance available to stricken homes
and businesses. By LAURA TOLLEY. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   BONNIE (Wilmington, N.C.) _ The season's first Atlantic
hurricane blows ashore near Wilmington, N.C., with winds of 115
mph. Forecasters expect the storm to gradually move back out to
sea. By TONY FREEMANTLE.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-COUCH (Lexington, Ky.) _ Kentucky quarterback Tim Couch just
may be the best college football player in the nation this season.
Yet few people outside of the state are familiar with the
record-setting quarterback who aims to put football on the map in a
state where basketball and horse racing rule. By BILL SULLIVAN.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ The Houston Astros try for their sixth
consecutive victory _ and 16th in the past 20 games _ as they wrap
up a two-game series against the Atlanta Braves at the Astrodome.
By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-ROBERTSON-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ The Clinton-Lewinsky debacle is
not the first scandal that has victimized the presidency. We look
at how it has been demeaned in the past. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
(Already filed)
