ATLANTA FALCONS 
1997: 7-9, 4-4 in NFC Central 
Coach (record): Dan Reeves (7-9 with Falcons, 148-115-1 overall) 
Stadium: Georgia Dome (71,228) 
Ticket information: (404) 223-8444 
Pieces in place 
QB Chris Chandler (20 passing TDs), Jamal Anderson (1,002 rushing
yards), WR Terance Mathis (802 receiving yards), OT Bob Whitfield,
DE Chuck Smith (12 sacks), DT Travis Hall (10.5 sacks), CB Ray
Buchanan (5 interceptions), MLB Jessie Tuggle (92 tackles). 
Key newcomers 
OT Corey Louchiey, WR Tony Martin, FS Eugene Robinson, LB Keith
Brooking, G/C Bob Hallen. 
Key losses 
DT Dan Owens, WR Bert Emanuel. 
Missing piece 
Protection for Chandler. In the first half of 1997, Chandler missed
two games and parts of four others with two concussions, an ankle
sprain and a bruised sternum. The Falcons went 1-7. He stayed
healthy and started in each of the final eight games as the club
was 6-2 down the stretch, and Chandler wound up in the Pro Bowl.
But the club did not do enough in the off-season to ensure the
consistency of the offensive line. They did sign Louchiey from
Buffalo, but he has been nothing to write home about, starting 13
of 45 games for a Bills club that had its own line problems. The
hope is that second-round pick Hallen of Kent State plays his way
into a starting position at guard. Veteran free agents such as Matt
Elliott and Dave Widell offer depth. But, despite the presence of
Whitfield at left tackle, the Falcons have a ways to go up front. 
Biggest test 
It is imperative that the Falcons get off to a fast start. They
started 0-5 in 1997 and 0-8 in 1996. The first five games of 1998
are at Carolina, vs. Philadelphia, at San Francisco, vs. Carolina
and at the New York Giants. 
Watch out for 
The Falcons' pass defense. The front four combined for 31 of the
club's 55 sacks in 1997. Three of the starters are back, including
Smith, who had 12 sacks. Despite the pressure up front, the Falcons
yielded 24 passing touchdowns. Only seven clubs were worse. To
strengthen the pass defense, Reeves signed Robinson, who brings
Super Bowl savvy to the secondary. Robinson will steady a unit that
includes DBs Buchanan and Ronnie Bradford. Both improved steadily
last season and combined for 29 passes defensed and nine
interceptions. 
Milestones 
With at least 72 points this season, place-kicker Morten Andersen
will move into the top two or three all-time scorers in the NFL. He
has 1,641 points, fifth on the all-time list. Minnesota's Gary
Anderson is fourth with 1,681 points. George Blanda is the all-time
leader with 2,002, Nick Lowery is second with 1,711, and Jan
Stenerud is third with 1,699. 
Overview 
Despite their strong close in 1997, the Falcons are a season or two
away from being considered legitimate title contenders. Chandler is
one of the best in the business if he is healthy. But he needs one
more playmaker on offense, and two or three on defense before he
can lead this club out of the abyss of four consecutive seasons
without a playoff berth. 
Prediction: 7-9 
 
