INDIANAPOLIS COLTS 
1997: 3-13, 2-6 in AFC East 
Coach (record): Jim Mora (first season with Colts, 93-74 overall) 
Stadium: RCA Dome (60,599) 
Ticket information: (317) 297-7000 
Pieces in place 
RB Marshall Faulk (1,054 yards), FB Zack Crockett, WR Marvin
Harrison (866 receiving yards), DE Tony Bennett, DE Dan Footman
(10.5 sacks), LB Quentin Coryatt (2 interceptions), FS Jason Belser
(2 interceptions). 
Key newcomers 
QB Peyton Manning, WR Jerome Pathon, CB Jeff Burris, LB Jeff
Herrod, G Tom Myslinski, WR Torrance Small. 
Key losses 
QB Jim Harbaugh, WR Sean Dawkins, WR Brian Stablein, G Doug
Widell. 
Missing piece 
Where have you gone, Lydell Mitchell? The Colts actually have a
great running back in five-year veteran Faulk, but the club has
strangely decided not to use him as much as they should. Well, to
keep the heat off of Manning, Faulk will need to carry the ball at
least 22 to 25 times a game. He has averaged 17.5 a game in his
career. The club will have to stay away from double-digit deficits,
where they are depending on the talented, but neophyte Manning. 
Biggest test 
We will get a good look at Manning's toughness in the first three
games of the season, when the Colts open at home against Miami,
before traveling to face New England and the New York Jets. Other
than that, Manning will get the benefit of facing 11 teams that
missed the playoffs in 1998. 
Watch out for 
The Colts' offensive line. If they fail, Manning's first year in
the NFL will be one he wants to forget. Tarik Glenn, the Colts'
first-round pick last year, is charged with playing left tackle to
protect Manning's blind side. Glenn played his rookie season at
right guard, so no one is 100 percent sure if he can block NFL
pass-rushing ends, even though he played left tackle in college.
The Colts made so many changes in the offensive line this spring
that C Jay Leeuwenburg will be the only player to play the same
position this season as he played last. 
Milestones 
K Cary Blanchard has scored more points (252) than any other player
in the league during the past two seasons. 
Overview 
Two seasons have passed since the Colts were one play away from
Super Bowl XXX. Despite last season's 3-13 record, they have enough
talent to be respectable at the very least. If Manning blooms
quickly, perhaps the Colts can make a serious run at the playoffs.
If not, look for another sub-.500 season. 
Prediction: 6-10 
 
Puzzle piece 
Peyton Manning 
 
