BALTIMORE RAVENS 
1997: 6-9-1, 3-5 in AFC Central 
Coach (record): Ted Marchibroda (10-21-1 with Ravens, 81-88-1
overall) 
Stadium: Ravens Stadium at Camden Yards (68,400) 
Ticket information: (410) 261-7283 
Pieces in place 
LT Jonathan Ogden, MLB Ray Lewis (4 sacks), OLB Peter Boulware
(11.5 sacks), WR Michael Jackson (918 receiving yards), DE Michael
McCrary (9 sacks). 
Key newcomers 
QB Jim Harbaugh, FB Roosevelt Potts, RB Errict Rhett, CB Rod
Woodson, CB Duane Starks, WR Pat Johnson. 
Key losses 
WR Derrick Alexander, RB Earnest Byner, CB Eugene Daniel, CB
Antonio Langham, RB Bam Morris. 
Missing piece 
The Ravens have the size on the offensive and defensive lines to
play with anyone. But their situation at wide receiver and
defensive back is questionable. At wide receiver, the club lost its
leading yardage man, Derrick Alexander, to Kansas City in free
agency. The other wide receiver, Michael Jackson, is coming off an
injury-plagued season. Baltimore drafted Oregon's Johnson in the
second round. But the club expects to go with Jackson and
second-year veteran Jermaine Lewis (648 yards, 6 TDs). In the
secondary, the club signed the aging Woodson; even with his age[
what is it?? ], Woodson is the club's best defensive back.
Baltimore drafted Miami's Starks in the first round, and he could
replace DeRon Jenkins if he does not improve. SS Stevon Moore had
off-season surgery on both knees. 
Biggest test 
Five of the Ravens' first eight games are against teams that went
to the playoffs in 1997: Jacksonville, the New York Giants,
Pittsburgh twice and Miami. 
Watch out for 
The Ravens are pinning their rebuilding hopes on outcasts Harbaugh
and Errict Rhett. In 1995, Harbaugh led the Indianapolis Colts
within one play of a Super Bowl berth, but quickly fell out of
favor. The feeling here is that he is at least better than the man
he replaced, Vinny Testaverde. But how much better? He doesn't have
the arm strength that Testaverde had, but he is more mobile and
coaches feel he is more of a take-charge guy in the fourth quarter.
Rhett had early success in Tampa Bay before a contract holdout and
rookie sensation Warrick Dunn cost him his job. Rhett is a two-time
1,000-yard rusher who reminds Marchibroda of great rushers he has
coached such as Lydell Mitchell and Thurman Thomas. 
Milestones 
The Ravens have not reached the playoffs since they were the
Cleveland Browns in 1994. 
Overview 
The Ravens play a fifth-place schedule, but it ranks as the
11th-toughest in the league. That's because they play in one of the
toughest divisions in the league. That alone will keep the Ravens
below .500, although they figure to show some improvement. 
Prediction: 5-11 
 
Puzzle piece 
RB Errict Rhett 
 
