<HEADLINE>
AFC WEST CAPSULES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
AFC WEST 
DENVER BRONCOS 
1997: 12-4, 6-2 in AFC West 
Coach (record): Mike Shanahan (37-16 with Broncos, 45-28 overall) 
Stadium: Mile High Stadium (76,078) 
Ticket information: (303) 433-7466 
Pieces in place 
QB John Elway (27 TDs), RB Terrell Davis (Super Bowl XXXII MVP,
1,750 rushing yards), TE Shannon Sharpe (1,107 receiving yards), WR
Rod Smith (1,180 receiving yards), DE Neil Smith (8.5 sacks), DT
Maa Tanuvasa (8.5 sacks), DE Alfred Williams (8.5 sacks), CB Ray
Crockett (4 interceptions), FS Steve Atwater (68 tackles). 
Key newcomers 
WR Marcus Nash, S Eric Brown, DE Marvin Washington, G Leo Goeas. 
Key losses 
LB Allen Aldridge, OT Jamie Brown, G Brian Habib. 
Missing piece 
The Broncos gave up chunks of yardage on the ground in 1997, but
the club's real concern is in the secondary. The club reluctantly
put KR Darrien Gordon at cornerback when the projected starter in
1997, Tory James, suffered a knee injury in the first preseason
game. James will start if he's healthy, but has never started an
NFL game yet. At strong safety, the Broncos may have to go with
rookie Brown of Mississippi State if the overachieving Tyrone
Braxton, 33, slows down. This questionable secondary will be asked
to cover the opposing wide receivers for an extra split second in
1998 because the pass rush is without one of its cogs. Williams
could be out until November because of a triceps injury. 
Biggest test 
From Nov. 16 to Dec. 21, the Broncos play four of six on the road
against Kansas City, San Diego, the New York Giants and Miami. 
Watch out for 
Davis will make another run at 2,000 yards. But the bigger story
out of Denver will be the farewell tour for Elway. And you can bet
that his teammates will play hard for him. But how bad does he
really want to win again? With that elusive Super Bowl championship
ring finally on his finger, will he take it easy during his last
season? Or does he try to go out with a bang? Whatever the case,
history is against him leading his club to a repeat title. None of
the retired quarterbacks with the 20 highest passer ratings in
league history won their last NFL playoff game. 
Milestones 
Elway has won 138 games as a starting quarterback, most in NFL
history. 
Overview 
The Broncos have been the AFC's best team for the past two years.
Nothing should change if the club stays healthy. Other AFC figure
to be much hungrier than the Broncos, and that could lead to their
demise as defending Super Bowl champions. Nevertheless, look for
Elway to at least make it to the AFC Championship Game in his final
season. And that is not a bad way to go out. 
Prediction: 13-3  
 
STARTING LINEUP 
Offense 
QB John Elway 
RB Terrell Davis 
FB Howard Griffith 
TE Shannon Sharpe 
WR Rod Smith 
WR Ed McCaffrey 
LT Tony Jones 
LG Mark Schlereth 
C Tom Nalen 
RG David Diaz-Infante 
RT Harry Swayne 
 
