RT Trevor Price 
LT Keith Traylor 
LE Neil Smith 
MLB Glenn Cadrez 
OLB Bill Romanowski 
OLB John Mobley 
CB Ray Crockett 
CB Darrien Gordon 
SS Tyrone Braxton 
FS Steve Atwater 
 
Specialists 
KR Vaughn Hebron 
PR Darrien Gordon 
K Jason Elam 
P Tom Rouen 
 
KANSAS CITY CHIEFS 
1997: 13-3, 7-1 in AFC West 
Coach (record): Marty Schottenheimer (97-56-1 with Chiefs, 143-87-1
overall) 
Stadium: Arrowhead Stadium (79,101) 
Ticket information: (816) 924-9400 
Pieces in place 
QB Elvis Grbac (1,943 passing yards), WR Andre Rison (1,092 yards,
7 TDs), NT Dan Williams (10.5 sacks), LB Derrick Thomas (9.5
sacks), Nickel CB Mark McMillan (8 interceptions), CB James Hasty
(3 interceptions, Pro Bowl), CB Dale Carter (2 interceptions, Pro
Bowl). 
Key newcomers 
DE Leslie O'Neal, DE Chester McGlockton, WR Derrick Alexander, OT
Victor Riley, RB Rashaan Shehee. 
Key loss 
RB Marcus Allen. 
Missing piece 
Despite the retirement of Allen and the waiving of Greg Hill,
Schottenheimer did not go after a running back in free agency, and
he passed on several in the first round of the draft. He'll put his
ground game hopes on a committee. HB Donnell Bennett, FB Kimble
Anders and second-round pick Shehee are the early candidates to get
most of the work. Schottenheimer even played speedy WR/KR Tamarick
Vanover at the position during the preseason. All are steady, but
none has shown much in the way of game-breaking ability. And that
could very well be the difference in the Chiefs' season: finding a
back who can turn a 4-yard run into an 80-yard touchdown dash. 
Biggest test 
The Chiefs play three of their final four games on the road, at
Denver, Dallas and Oakland. Each of the Chiefs' three losses in
1997 came on the road. 
Watch out for 
The club's play at quarterback was a big issue in 1997. Elvis Grbac
was the starter, but Rich Gannon led the team to a 5-1 record when
Grbac sat because of a broken collarbone. Grbac came back for the
playoffs, but his play against Denver in the playoff loss was
nothing special. Grbac is the starter in 1998, and the club is
expected to allow him to call more audibles. And Grbac has more
weapons to work with. Alexander (1,009 yards, 9 TDs) pairs with
Rison to give the Chiefs one of the most potent duo of wide
receivers in the league, if Alexander can shake off a ribcage
injury. 
Milestones 
With a starting record of 14-5, Grbac has the best winning
percentage (.737) as a starter among active NFL quarterbacks. 
Overview 
The Chiefs have the defense and passing game to beat any team. If
the running game produces, perhaps this club can attain home-field
advantage in the playoffs again. Whatever happens, this club will
only be judged by what they do in the playoffs. And maybe this is
the year that a Schottenheimer team goes all the way. Prediction:
12-4 
 
STARTING LINEUP 
Offense 
QB Elvis Grbac 
RB Donnell Bennett 
