SEATTLE SEAHAWKS 
1997: 8-8, 4-4 in AFC West 
Coach (record): Dennis Erickson (23-25) 
Stadium: Kingdome (66,400) 
Ticket information: (888) NFL-HAWK 
Pieces in place 
WR Joey Galloway (1,049 yards, 12 TDs), DE Michael Sinclair (12
sacks), DT Cortez Kennedy, FS Daryl Williams (8 interceptions), LB
Chad Brown (6.5 sacks). 
Key newcomers 
RB Ricky Watters, LB Darrin Smith, G Brian Habib, C Kevin Glover,
LB Anthony Simmons, P Jeff Feagles, RB Ahman Green. 
Key losses 
C Kevin Mawae, RB Lamar Smith, RB Chris Warren, P Rick Tuten. 
Missing piece 
The Seahawks were one of four teams to finish in the top 10 in
total offense and total defense. But they were the only team of
that foursome _ Denver, Green Bay and Pittsburgh were the others _
that missed the playoffs. One of the reasons was because of the
Seahawks' disastrous special teams. Two losses came because of
missed field goals in overtime. Two fumbles were returned for
touchdowns. One punt went minus-6 yards. A punt was blocked for a
safety. A dropped punt snap that set up a touchdown. In the
off-season, the Seahawks added a new special-teams coach (Pete
Rodriguez), a new punter and holder (Feagles), a new kickoff
returner (Green) and a new deep snapper (Jason McEndoo). Galloway
and CB Shawn Springs are also expected to challenge incumbent
Ronnie Harris for the punt-return job. Still, kicker Todd Peterson,
who missed those two overtime field goals, remains. And if this
team is to take it to the next level, he'll have to be perfect, or
close to it, in close games. 
Biggest test 
The Seahawks play six consecutive games against division foes from
Oct. 4 to Nov. 15. 
Watch out for 
How Jon Kitna performs as this club's starting quarterback if
41-year-old Warren Moon retires or gets hurt. The wide receivers
are there with Galloway and Mike Pritchard, and so is the running
game with Watters. Much of Kitna's or Moon's success will depend on
the offensive line, which is probably this club's only spot of
contention. It is solid, with Pro Bowl center Glover and Habib.
There is potential for greatness with LT Walter Jones and LG Pete
Kendall. Both are young, and since they protect the quarterback's
blind side, any mistake could lead to injury. 
Milestones 
The Seahawks have not posted a winning record since 1990. 
Overview 
This team has the talent to reach the playoffs, and with a schedule
that ranks as the 23rd ``toughest,'' in the NFL, there should be no
excuses. To be sure, there is a question at quarterback. But
billionaire-owner Paul Allen didn't dig deep in his pockets to
field a team that is only competitive. He wants a winner. If one is
not produced, this could be Erickson's last year. Prediction: 9-7 
 
STARTING LINEUP 
Offense 
QB Warren Moon 
RB Ricky Watters 
FB Mack Strong 
TE Christian Fauria 
WR Joey Galloway 
WR Mike Pritchard 
LT Walter Jones 
LG Pete Kendall 
C Kevin Glover 
